Queens Boulevard, at the S.W. corner of 63rd Drive (formerly Penelope Street (right not shown), showing the L. Suydam House. Some of the owners were: L. Suydam 1852; D. Droge 1860; J. P. L. Sperr

May 24, 1935

63rd Drive, east side, between Queens Boulevard and Saunders Street. This old dwelling was owned by Aug. F. Schrader in 1909 and 63rd Drive was then known as Remsen Street. In 1891 A. F. Shrader owned the property, according to Wolverton's Atlas of that year.

P. L. Sperr

Squatters (Queens): Shacks of the unemployed, not an uncommon sight during the height of the depression. View 1 is at Second Street and Astoria Boulevard; view 2, at Grand Central Parkway and Pell Avenue; and view 3, at Queens Boulevard and 63rd Drive.

P. L. Sperr
